    {
      "id": "PopularPost214662",
      "post_content": "Believe it or not, I once nearly beat my opponent with this piece of crap. He had no flying or reach creatures, so I was dealing 2 damage every turn while my [Amphin Cutthroat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Amphin Cutthroat)s and [Bird Maiden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bird Maiden)s blocked the attacks from his hoard of zombies. And when he tried to [Victim of Night](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Victim of Night) my [Dementia Bat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dementia Bat), I simply tapped five and sacrificed it, forcing him to discard the last two cards in his hand.  \nHonestly, if he had played that [Endless Ranks of the Dead](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Endless Ranks of the Dead) one turn later, I would have killed him w/ my [Dementia Bat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dementia Bat).",
